data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Chocolatey is a program that installs Windows software — any Windows software, no matter how difficult it can be to install manually or how adware-laden its installer is.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Chocolatey is based on the concept of packages, which are files that contain instructions on how to download, install, and uninstall a specific application. All Chocolatey packages are manually reviewed to ensure that they work properly and are free of spyware and adware.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: This installer will install the latest version of Chocolatey, as well as ChocolateyGUI, an application that enables you to find and install software through Chocolatey using a windowed interface. (Without ChocolateyGUI, you must use the command line to interact with Chocolatey.)

data.name: label6.Text
data.value: Chocolatey will be installed into the below directory. Note that you should use the default value unless you have a very good reason to do otherwise (this decision has security implications).

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: Congratulations! Chocolatey has been successfully installed.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: Look for ChocolateyGUI on your Start menu or screen. Or, use the "choco" command from an elevated (Administrator) Command Prompt window.
